EMERGING INFECTIOUS DISEASES: ADVANCE DISPATCHES, OCT. 1997
***********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Fri, 3 Oct 1997 14:38:00-0400
From: EID Listserver Manager <EIDLISTMGR@cdc.gov>

The new Advanced Articles from EMERGING DISEASES (EID) are now available.
See instructions below for information on obtaining these articles
electronically. Adobe Acrobat and PostScript versions are not available at
this time.
--------------------------------------------------
Emerging Infectious Diseases * Volume 3 * Number 4
--------------------------------------------------
Advanced Articles
* Produce Handling and Processing Practices, Larry R. Beuchat and Jee-Hoon Ryu
* Identifying and Controlling Emerging Foodborne Pathogens: Research Needs,
Robert L. Buchanan
*Impact of Changing Consumer Lifestyles on the Emergence/Reemergence of
Foodborne Pathogens, Janet E. Collins
* Communicating Foodborne Disease Risk, Baruch Fischhoff and Julie S. Downs
Available through:
<http://fpt/cdc/gov/ncidod/EID/advance.htm>
ftp://ftp.cdc.gov/pub/EID/vol3no4/
------------------------
Suggested Citation Style
------------------------
Suggested citation for articles made available electronically before the
full issue of the journal is published:
Example: Morse SS. Factors in the emergence of infectious diseases. Emerg
Infect Dis [serial online] 1995 Jan-Mar [cited 1996 Jun 5]; 1[(1):[24
screens]. Available from URL: <http://www.cdc.gov/ncidod/EID/eid.htm>
--------------------------
To subscribe to EID-TOC, send a message to LISTSERV@CDC.GOV with the
following in the body of your message: SUBSCRIBE EID-TOC
